#import "../template.typ": *

= 
Let $cal(V)$ define the linear space containing all real functions on the interval $[-1, 1]$ that are constant on all four subdomains $[-1, -1/2)", "[-1/2, 0)", "[0, 1/2)", "[1/2, 1]$

(a) Give an orthogonal base in $cal(V)$ with the scalar product
$
  innerp(u, v) = integral_(-1)^1 u(x) v(x) dif x
$

(b) Let $u(x) = x^2 - x$. Determine $v in cal(V)$ so that
$
  integral_(-1)^1 abs(u(x) - v(x))^2 dif x
$
is minimized.

(c) Determine the lowest possible value of the integral in (b).

#solution[
  (a) 
]